1. What is React Js?
React.js is a JavaScript library for building user interfaces, primarily for single-page applications.

2. What is NPM in React Js?
NPM (Node Package Manager) is used to manage and install dependencies for React projects.

3. What is Role of Node Js in React Js?
Node.js provides a runtime environment for executing JavaScript outside the browser and is used for building and running React development tools.

4. What is CLI command In React Js?
CLI commands allow you to create and manage React projects. Example:

sh
Copy code
npx create-react-app my-app
5. What is Components in React Js?
Components are reusable UI elements in React, defined as JavaScript functions or classes.

6. What is Header and Content Components in React Js?
Header Component: Renders the header section.
Content Component: Renders the main content area.
7. How to Install React Js on Windows and Linux Operating Systems?
Windows:
Install Node.js (includes NPM) from nodejs.org.
Create a React app:
sh
Copy code
npx create-react-app my-app
Check NPM version:
sh
Copy code
npm -v
Linux:
Install Node.js and NPM:
sh
Copy code
sudo apt install nodejs npm
Create a React app:
sh
Copy code
npx create-react-app my-app
Check NPM version:
sh
Copy code
npm -v
8. How to Check Version of React Js?
sh
Copy code
npm list react
9. How to Change in Components of React Js?
Example: Modify Header component.

jsx
Copy code
import React from 'react';

function Header() {
  return (
    <header>
      <h1>My New Header</h1>
    </header>
  );
}

export default Header;
10. How to Create a List View in React Js?
Example: Create a list view component.

jsx
Copy code
import React from 'react';

const ListView = ({ items }) => {
  return (
    <ul>
      {items.map((item, index) => (
        <li key={index}>{item}</li>
      ))}
    </ul>
  );
};

export default ListView;
11. Create Increment Decrement State Change by Button Click
Example: Create a counter component.

jsx
Copy code
import React, { useState } from 'react';

const Counter = () => {
  const [count, setCount] = useState(0);

  return (
    <div>
      <p>Count: {count}</p>
      <button onClick={() => setCount(count + 1)}>Increment</button>
      <button onClick={() => setCount(count - 1)}>Decrement</button>
    </div>
  );
};

export default Counter;
Complete these tasks to gain a fundamental understanding of React.js and its basic functionalities.
